snippet: The results of Tuesday’s presidential election left many Israelis questioning whether Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu had risked their collective relationship with Washington.
abstract: Israeli Prime Min Benjamin Netanyahu rushes to repair his relationship with Pres Obama in wake of his re-election victory; many Israelis are questioning whether Netanyahu has risked their collective relationship with United States by confronting and even undercutting Obama in the past.

byline.contributor: Thomas Erdbrink contributed reporting from Amsterdam, and Isabel Kershner from Jerusalem.

lead_paragraph: The results of Tuesday’s presidential election left many Israelis questioning whether Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu had risked their collective relationship with Washington.

headline.main: Netanyahu Rushes to Repair Damage With Obama
headline.print_headline:
Netanyahu Rushes
To Repair Damage
